 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Keyword Co-occurrence Network – Gephi Export\n",
    "\n",
    "Builds a keyword co-occurrence network from YouTube comments for each Google product. Two keywords are connected if they appear in the same comment. The resulting nodes/edges CSVs can be opened directly in Gephi for network visualization.\n",
    "\n",
   
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import re\n",
    "import itertools\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "from collections import defaultdict\n",
    "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import ENGLISH_STOP_WORDS\n",
    "import networkx as nx"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Load all 6 CSVs from GitHub repo"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "rows loaded: 3253\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def load_csv(path, product, period):\n",
    "    df = pd.read_csv(path)\n",
    "    df['product'] = product\n",
    "    df['period'] = period\n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "frames = [\n",
    "    load_csv('old_stadia_youtube_comments_raw.csv',          'stadia',       'before'),\n",
    "    load_csv('recent_stadia_youtube_comments_raw.csv',       'stadia',       'after'),\n",
    "    load_csv('old_google_glass_youtube_comments_raw.csv',    'google_glass', 'before'),\n",
    "    load_csv('recent_google_glass_youtube_comments_raw.csv', 'google_glass', 'after'),\n",
    "    load_csv('old_plus_youtube_comments_raw.csv',            'google_plus',  'before'),\n",
    "    load_csv('recent_plus_youtube_comments_raw.csv',         'google_plus',  'after'),\n",
    "]\n",
    "df = pd.concat(frames, ignore_index=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "def clean(text):\n",
    "    text = str(text)\n",
    "    text = re.sub(r'http\\S+', '', text)\n",
    "    text = re.sub(r'[^\\w\\s]', ' ', text)\n",
    "    return re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text).strip().lower()\n",
    "\n",
    "df['clean_comment'] = df['comment'].apply(clean)\n",
    "df = df.drop_duplicates(subset=['clean_comment'])\n",
    "df['word_count'] = df['clean_comment'].apply(lambda x: len(x.split()))\n",
    "df = df[df['word_count'] >= 4].reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "print('rows loaded:', len(df))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Build co-occurrence network per product\n",
    "\n",
    "For each product, we identify the top 30 most frequent keywords, then count how often any two keywords appear in the same comment. Pairs that co-occur at least 3 times become edges in the network."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "stadia: 30 nodes, 239 edges\n",
      "google_glass: 30 nodes, 84 edges\n",
      "google_plus: 30 nodes, 104 edges\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "custom_stops = set(ENGLISH_STOP_WORDS) | {\n",
    "    'google','stadia','glass','plus','would','could','really','just',\n",
    "    'like','know','think','still','even','back','one','get','got',\n",
    "    'make','made','want','way','also','much','never','said','going',\n",
    "    'come','came','thing','people','time','year','years','new','good',\n",
    "    'great','don','didn','isn','wasn','that','this','they','their',\n",
    "    'have','been','will','with','from','for','are','was'\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_top_words(texts, n=30):\n",
    "    freq = defaultdict(int)\n",
    "    for text in texts:\n",
    "        words = [w for w in text.split() if len(w) > 3 and w not in custom_stops]\n",
    "        for w in words:\n",
    "            freq[w] += 1\n",
    "    return set([w for w,c in sorted(freq.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:n]])\n",
    "\n",
    "networks = {}\n",
    "for prod in ['stadia', 'google_glass', 'google_plus']:\n",
    "    subset = df[df['product'] == prod]['clean_comment']\n",
    "    top_words = get_top_words(subset, n=30)\n",
    "    edge_counts = defaultdict(int)\n",
    "    for text in subset:\n",
    "        words = list(set([w for w in text.split() if w in top_words]))\n",
    "        for w1, w2 in itertools.combinations(sorted(words), 2):\n",
    "            edge_counts[(w1, w2)] += 1\n",
    "    edges = [(w1, w2, c) for (w1, w2), c in edge_counts.items() if c >= 3]\n",
    "    networks[prod] = {'nodes': top_words, 'edges': edges}\n",
    "    print(f'{prod}: {len(top_words)} nodes, {len(edges)} edges')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Export to Gephi-compatible CSV files\n",
    "\n",
   
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "gephi_nodes.csv: 90 nodes\n",
      "gephi_edges.csv: 427 edges\n",
      "Upload both files to Gephi: Data Laboratory → Import Spreadsheet\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "all_nodes = []\n",
    "all_edges = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for prod in networks:\n",
    "    for word in networks[prod]['nodes']:\n",
    "        freq = sum(1 for text in df[df['product']==prod]['clean_comment'] if word in text.split())\n",
    "        all_nodes.append({'Id': f'{prod}_{word}', 'Label': word, 'product': prod, 'frequency': freq})\n",
    "    for w1, w2, weight in networks[prod]['edges']:\n",
    "        all_edges.append({'Source': f'{prod}_{w1}', 'Target': f'{prod}_{w2}',\n",
    "                          'Weight': weight, 'product': prod})\n",
    "\n",
    "nodes_df = pd.DataFrame(all_nodes)\n",
    "edges_df = pd.DataFrame(all_edges)\n",
    "\n",
    "nodes_df.to_csv('gephi_nodes.csv', index=False)\n",
    "edges_df.to_csv('gephi_edges.csv', index=False)\n",
    "print(f'gephi_nodes.csv: {len(nodes_df)} nodes')\n",
    "print(f'gephi_edges.csv: {len(edges_df)} edges')\n",
    "print('Upload both files to Gephi: Data Laboratory → Import Spreadsheet')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Preview network in Python (NetworkX)\n",
    "\n",
    "This gives a quick visual before opening in Gephi."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1800x600 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "saved network_preview.png\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 6))\n",
    "prod_labels = {'stadia': 'Google Stadia', 'google_glass': 'Google Glass', 'google_plus': 'Google+'}\n",
    "colors = {'stadia': 'steelblue', 'google_glass': 'seagreen', 'google_plus': 'tomato'}\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, prod in enumerate(['stadia', 'google_glass', 'google_plus']):\n",
    "    ax = axes[i]\n",
    "    G = nx.Graph()\n",
    "    G.add_nodes_from(networks[prod]['nodes'])\n",
    "    for w1, w2, weight in networks[prod]['edges']:\n",
    "        G.add_edge(w1, w2, weight=weight)\n",
    "    pos = nx.spring_layout(G, seed=42, k=0.8)\n",
    "    node_sizes = [G.degree(n) * 80 + 100 for n in G.nodes()]\n",
    "    edge_weights = [G[u][v]['weight'] * 0.3 for u,v in G.edges()]\n",
    "    nx.draw_networkx_nodes(G, pos, ax=ax, node_size=node_sizes,\n",
    "                           node_color=colors[prod], alpha=0.8)\n",
    "    nx.draw_networkx_edges(G, pos, ax=ax, width=edge_weights, alpha=0.4)\n",
    "    nx.draw_networkx_labels(G, pos, ax=ax, font_size=7)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(prod_labels[prod])\n",
    "    ax.axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Keyword Co-occurrence Networks (preview – open gephi_nodes/edges.csv in Gephi for full visualization)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('network_preview.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print('saved network_preview.png')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Network centrality (SNA metrics)\n",
    "\n",
    "Following Lecture 8, we calculate degree centrality and betweenness centrality to identify the most connected and influential keywords in the discussion network."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "stadia\n",
      "  top degree centrality (hubs): ['games', 'game', 'gaming', 'internet', 'play']\n",
      "  top betweenness (brokers):    ['video', 'games', 'game', 'gaming', 'internet']\n",
      "\n",
      "google_glass\n",
      "  top degree centrality (hubs): ['glasses', 'tech', 'actually', 'video', 'vision']\n",
      "  top betweenness (brokers):    ['glasses', 'video', 'actually', 'look', 'tech']\n",
      "\n",
      "google_plus\n",
      "  top degree centrality (hubs): ['video', 'youtube', 'comment', 'social', 'used']\n",
      "  top betweenness (brokers):    ['video', 'youtube', 'right', 'comments', 'comment']\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for prod in ['stadia', 'google_glass', 'google_plus']:\n",
    "    G = nx.Graph()\n",
    "    G.add_nodes_from(networks[prod]['nodes'])\n",
    "    for w1, w2, weight in networks[prod]['edges']:\n",
    "        G.add_edge(w1, w2, weight=weight)\n",
    "    degree = sorted(nx.degree_centrality(G).items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:5]\n",
    "    between = sorted(nx.betweenness_centrality(G).items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:5]\n",
    "    print(f'\\n{prod}')\n",
    "    print('  top degree centrality (hubs):', [w for w,s in degree])\n",
    "    print('  top betweenness (brokers):   ', [w for w,s in between])"
   ]
  }
 ],
